<section class="jobs">
  <a id="careers"></a>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
      <h1>Job Openings</h1>
      <p>It takes world-class talent to build a global powerhouse. Join our growing team.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row titles hidden-xs">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-2">Location</div>
    <div class="col-sm-9 col-md-10">Job Title</div>
  </div>
  <div class="positions">
        <article class="job js-title">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-2">New York </div>
        <div class="col-sm-9 col-md-10">
          <div class="row no-gutter">
            <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-10">
              <h2 class="title"><a href="#">Assistant Ad Operations Manager</a></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-2 text-right">
              <a href="https://purch.applytojob.com/apply/yFdklq60dR/Assistant-Ad-Operations-Manager" class="btn-apply"><span class="hidden-xs">Apply </span><i class="fa fa-angle-right fa-lg"></i></a>
            </div>    
          </div>
          <div class="row no-gutter article-content js-article-content">
            <div class="col-sm-12">
              <p>Purch is seeking an organized assistant ad operations manager to work with the direct sales team. This role is responsible for supporting the team from pre- to post-sales cycle for an assigned list of digital campaigns. The assistant ad ops manager will serve as liaison between sales, account management, and the design teams to ensure campaign fulfillment and client satisfaction. The ideal candidate will have a detailed knowledge of digital media, ad serving, and ad tech. This is a fabulous opportunityÂ for someone looking to join a fast growing, innovative, and dynamic digital media organization.</p>
<p><strong>The Day to Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Responsible for set up and monitoring and project management of ad campaigns from launch to final reporting</li>
<li>QA campaign creative for spec compliance and proper functionality</li>
<li>Support pre-sales efforts with sales planning and creative solutions teams â including inventory management, technical capabilities, and ad specs</li>
<li>Advise sales and clients on best practices for campaign delivery, workflow improvement and technical</li>
<li>Coordinate with development and engineering teams on implementing custom sponsorships and integrations</li>
<li>Assist finance with internal and 3rd party delivery reporting to ensure proper revenue reconciliation</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Must Haves</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1-2 years of experience in an ad operations role such as an ad trafficker, ad network or DSP support.</li>
<li>Experience with publisher ad-serving and ad management technologies (DFP preferred).</li>
<li>Knowledge of 3rd party ad tags.</li>
<li>Working knowledge of Excel, familiarity with HTML.</li>
<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with a flexible, personable attitude and customer service mindset</li>
<li>Effective time management skills: ability to prioritize and meet deadlines</li>
<li>Ability to work well independently and within a team environment</li>
<li>Bachelor degree required</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About Purch</strong></p>
<p>Purch is one of the worldâs largest tech review publishers with brands such as Tomâs Guide,Â LaptopMag,Â and LiveScience under its umbrella. With billions of users and three straight years of profitable,Â venture-backed double-digit growth,Â Purch is on a mission to make complex buying decisions easier for both buyers and sellers. Purch is a fun,Â close-knit,Â flexible,Â results-oriented work environment looking for talented people who fit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
        <article class="job js-title">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-2">New York </div>
        <div class="col-sm-9 col-md-10">
          <div class="row no-gutter">
            <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-10">
              <h2 class="title"><a href="#">Senior Software Engineer</a></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-2 text-right">
              <a href="https://purch.applytojob.com/apply/PwHSuaPuIB/Senior-Software-Engineer" class="btn-apply"><span class="hidden-xs">Apply </span><i class="fa fa-angle-right fa-lg"></i></a>
            </div>    
          </div>
          <div class="row no-gutter article-content js-article-content">
            <div class="col-sm-12">
              <p>Purch is one of the worldâs largest tech review publishers with brands such as Tomâs Guide, LaptopMag, and LiveScience under its umbrella. With billions of users and three straight years of profitable, venture-backed double digit growth, Purch is on a mission to make complex buying decisions easier for both buyers and sellers.Â  Purch is a fun, close-knit, flexible, results-oriented work environment looking for talented people who fit.</p>
<p>This position will be responsible for supporting and enhancing multiple REST APIs providing data and functionality to various Purch web properties and mobile applications. The Senior Software Engineer will work with product managers, project managers, mobile developers, and other backend developers to provide REST endpoints that provide the necessary data and functionality required for the efficient operation of all sites and mobile applications.</p>
<p>The APIs handle millions of requests per day across all major mobile platforms and top web properties such as TomsGuide.com, TomsHardware.com, TopTenReviews.com and others. The developer must be experienced with the design and implementation of highly scalable fault-tolerant REST API infrastructures.</p>
<p>We are looking for a highly motivated individual who can work well as part of an experienced, tight-knit team. The ability to collaborate with other developers and work within an Agile/SCRUM process is critical.</p>
<p>Purch employs a diverse set of technologies to meet functional and performance requirements. Breadth of experience and the ability to learn new technologies quickly and thoroughly is critical for this role.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Work with product managers, project managers, mobile developers, and other backend developers to provide the necessary functionality and performance to handle hundreds of requests per second around the clock.</li>
<li>Ensure that all APIs function at an extremely high level â including efficient payloads, fast response times, and near zero down time.</li>
<li>Ensure test coverage for all critical code paths.</li>
<li>Document features, designs, and implementation decisions.</li>
<li>Proactively seek clarification of requirements and recommend alternatives to speed delivery and/or enhance design.</li>
<li>Be comfortable working on the backend, frontend or in between.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Practical knowledge and use of design patterns.</li>
<li>5+ years developing C# ASP.NET applications (.Net Core preferred).</li>
<li>5+ years SQL experience (Postgres, MySQL)</li>
<li>2+ years ElasticSearch or Solr</li>
<li>2+ years Node.js (TypeScript preferred)</li>
<li>Git + BitBucket (or GitHub) â especially branching, forking, tagging, and pull requests.</li>
<li>Unit Testing.</li>
<li>Deep knowledge of HTTP requests and responses.</li>
<li>Knowledge of how HTTP requests and responses are routed over the internet (including routing, caching, port usage, etc.).</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Full Stack development experience</li>
